profile_description:Colombia Huila Betania Chiloso Washed COE\vVariety: Chiloso | Altitude: 1800-1900m\vMoisture: 12% (nominal), est. ~10-10.5% (aged 8mo)\vDensity: Unknown (est. 840-870g/L)\vLoad: 120g\v\vVersion 1 - Based on Kaffelogic official F-WSH 1500-2200\v(SeanBrews v2.2) as primary template.\v\vAdjustments from official template:\v- Preheat 840->790W (aged bean, lower moisture ~10%,\v  reduced heat demand)\v- expect_fc 206->204C (1800m is lower end of range,\v  aged bean may crack slightly earlier)\v- expect_colrchange set to 168C\v- Kd 3.55->3.10 (proven stable from Catimor V5/V3)\v- min_ROR 2.0->0.4 (safer, from ETH V1 experience)\v- Cooldown 17000/16000/85C (light roast fast lock)\v- Roast levels shifted down for light roast target\v\vRoast profile and fan profile kept from official\vF-WSH 1500-2200 template. No Zone control.\vSchema 1.4.\v\vExpected FC: ~198-204C (est. based on altitude)\v\vRecommended Levels:\v\vLight Clean: Level 1.5 (~202C, ~12% dev)\vLight Balanced: Level 2.0 (~204C, ~15% dev) <- Target\vMedium Light: Level 2.5 (~206C, ~17% dev)\v\vAging note: Bean stored 8+ months in dry climate.\vTop notes may be muted. If cup is flat/papery,\vtry Level 2.5 for more development.\v\vC40 pour-over grind: 24-28 clicks\vResting period: 5-14 days (aged bean: shorter OK)\v
